nodes.text: A male Mandalorian was part of the Death Watch during the Clone Wars. A right hand man of Pre Vizsla, the leader of the Death Watch forces based around the moon of Mandalore, Concordia, he was sent to Coruscant based on a suggestion by Count Dooku of the Confederacy of Independent Systems to assassinate the Duchess of Mandalore, Satine Kryze, leader of the New Mandalorian reformist movement. Once there, the assassin hunted Satine, first attempting to kill her by sabotaging her speeder. He eventually framed her for the murder of an informant, Davu Golec, who the assassin had shot with a sniper rifle. The assassin fought Satine's friend, Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi, during another attempt to kill her, and was defeated by him. Ultimately, the assassin was unsuccessful in his quest.

The Unidentified Death Watch assassin made his first appearance in the Star Wars: The Clone Wars animated series, in the episode "Duchess of Mandalore." In the episode he was voiced by Dee Bradley Baker, who also provided the voices for all of the clone troopers in the show.
